description: Takeaways will be allowed to operate and places of worship to open after 15 days of no new cases.
title: Coronavirus: Guernsey to ease lockdown further
title_page: Coronavirus: Guernsey to ease lockdown further - BBC News
maintext: Director of Public Health Dr Nicola Brink said the strategy of "test, trace and quarantine" would remain in place as it "continues to be effective as evidenced in the lack of new positives and the low number of active cases".
